250 g Ground Beef
170 g Orzo
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
113 g Baby Heirloom Tomatoes
7 g Basil
1 unit(s) Zucchini
¼ cup Sun-Dried Tomato Pesto
4.3 g Italian Seasoning
7.5 g Beef Stock Powder
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Halve zucchini lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.

Heat a large pot over medium-high.
When the pot is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, beef and zucchini. Cook for 4-6 min, stirring often and breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Carefully drain and discard excess fat. Season with salt and pepper.

Add orzo. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine.
Add stock powder, Italian Seasoning and 2 1/2 cups (4 cups) water. Bring to a boil over high.
Reduce heat to medium. Cook uncovered for 10-12 min, stirring occasionally, until orzo is tender but still firm to the bite.

Thinly slice basil.
Halve tomatoes.

Once orzo is tender, add pesto, basil and tomatoes. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until combined. Season with salt and pepper.
Divide orzo between bowls.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.